  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "`index.yaml` files, as generated by `helm repo index`, are not written atomically. As a result files can be half-written when helm or another client reads them.\r\n\r\nThis is an example of a custom YAML scanner breaking because of a half-written file:\r\n```\r\n/<redacted>/path/to/scanner.py\", line 319, in scan_index\r\n\"could not find expected ':'\", self.get_mark())\r\nyaml.scanner.ScannerError: while scanning a simple key\r\nin \"<unicode string>\", line 3497, column 5:\r\nappVersi\r\n^\r\ncould not find expected ':'\r\nin \"<unicode string>\", line 3497, column 13:\r\nappVersi\r\n^\r\n```\r\n",
